# label: TOOL
# role: supports feature — hydration benchmark + IN-clause size limit probe

Two modes: normal run measures the two-trip pattern (search → hydrate) at
realistic sizes; -limit-test pushes the IN(?, ?, ...) clause up past 1M to
find SQLite's actual ceiling. Reads from /tmp/gopher_bench.db — pair with
cmd/gen_test_data first.
